{
  "stem": "26765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And yes, I did speak about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I did not hide it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They always knew that I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But when they were small, I was still searching so that unfortunately, I could not give them clear direction, not only that, I had married a Catholic man.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when the marriage didn't work out and we got divorced, the divorce decree ordered me to raise the children Catholic.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was afraid if I did not that I would lose the children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they went to Catholic school and well, the Ten Commandments are the same in both religions.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I stressed that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I stressed the belief in one God, which is also in the Catholic religion.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I stressed the importance of learning, of trying to understand, which I think is part of the Jewish tradition, the learning.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I stressed the importance of having an understanding and an empathy for those less fortunate and to not just give charity, but to also make sure that people preserve their dignity, which I think is a Jewish way of giving.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so I taught those things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I studied.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I read a lot about Jewish thought, Jewish philosophy, Martin Buber, Leo Baeck, but it wasn't until I was about 40 that I found a temple where I felt comfortable.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that I found and I'm very happy about that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was right after the fall of communism, and I wanted to go and see Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I went to Bergen-Belsen, and when I got there, I was looking for things to read because I didn't have to look at the pictures that were hanging there in the vestibule.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew what that was like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I went up to the desk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I sat there for a while.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
